What do you notice in the plot?

Response:

Coord_trans()

Notes: The difference between transforming the scales and transforming the coordinate system is that scale transformation occurs BEFORE statistics, and coordinate transformation afterwards. Coordinate transformation also changes the shape of geoms:

?coord_trans
## starting httpd help server ...
##  done
ggplot(aes(x= age, y = friend_count), data =pf)+
  geom_jitter(alpha =1/20)+
  xlim(13,90)+
  coord_trans(x = "sqrt")
## Warning: Removed 5159 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Look up the documentation for coord_trans() and add a layer to the plot that transforms friend_count using the square root function. Create your plot!

use position = position_jitter(h = 0) to set the y value higher than 0 after the jitter

ggplot(aes(x= age, y = friend_count), data =pf)+
  geom_point(alpha = 1/20, position = position_jitter(h = 0))+
  xlim(13,90)+
  coord_trans(x = "sqrt", y= "sqrt")
## Warning: Removed 5182 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

          n = n())

pf.f_by_age <- pf %>%
  group_by(age) %>%
  summarise(friend_counts_mean = mean(friend_count),
            friend_counts_median = median(friend_count),
            n =n()) %>%
  arrange(age)

qplot(age, friend_counts_mean, data = pf.f_by_age)

Age with Months Means

pf$age_with_months <-pf$age + (1 - pf$dob_month / 12)

Programming Assignment

pf.fc_by_age_months <- pf %>%
group_by(age_with_months) %>%
summarise(friend_counts_mean = mean(friend_count),
          friend_counts_median = median(friend_count),
          n =n()) %>%
arrange(age_with_months)

qplot(age_with_months, friend_counts_mean, data = pf.fc_by_age_months)

age_month_group <- group_by(pf, age_with_months) 
pf.fc_by_age_months <- summarise(age_month_group,

                                 n = n()) 
pf.fc_by_age_months <- arrange(pf.fc_by_age_months, age_with_months)

Smoothing Conditional Means

Notes:

p1 <- ggplot(aes(x= age, y = friend_count_mean),data = pf.fc_by_age)+
  geom_line()

p2 <- ggplot(aes(x = age_with_months, y=friend_count_mean),data = subset(pf.fc_by_age_months,age_with_months<71))+geom_line()

library(gridExtra)
## Warning: package 'gridExtra' was built under R version 3.3.2
## 
## Attaching package: 'gridExtra'
## The following object is masked from 'package:dplyr':
## 
##     combine
grid.arrange(p2,p1,ncol = 1)

### want to make 2.5 yr together
p3 <- ggplot(aes((x = round(age/5)*5), y = friend_count), data = subset(pf,age<71))+
               geom_line(stat='summary', fun.y = mean)

grid.arrange(p3,p2,p1,ncol = 1)

### geom_smooth make it smooth
p1 <- p1 + geom_smooth()
p2 <- p2 + geom_smooth()
grid.arrange(p3,p2,p1,ncol = 1)
